HEADWORD: Glans
<hw>Glans</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Glandes</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. See
<er>Gland</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The vascular body which forms the
apex of the penis, and the extremity of the clitoris.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The acorn or mast of the oak and
similar fruits.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Goiter.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A pessary.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glare</ent>⟦br⟧
